-parents-kids-rules-responsible-age-moderation-2025-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoblox%3C%2Fa%3E%20swears%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESebastian%20Barrios%2C%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20engineering%20at%20the%20gaming%20platform%2C%20said%20he%20sends%20his%20CEO%20a%20weekly%20email%20outlining%20his%20accomplishments%2C%20what's%20next%20on%20his%20plate%2C%20and%20where%20he%20needs%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20me%20keep%20track%20of%20what's%20working%2C%20what's%20not%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20Barrios%20said%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BLenny's%20Podcast%26quot%3B%20published%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20actually%20have%20an%20expectation%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20send%20that%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20something%20I%20do%20myself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20a%20simple%20habit%20that%20has%20freed%20up%20one-on-one%20meetings%20for%20higher-level%20strategy%20instead%20of%20routine%20check-ins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarrios%20also%20said%20he%20sends%20this%20weekly%20email%20to%20his%20broader%20team%20to%20keep%20everyone%20aligned%20on%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20usually%20also%20get%20feedback%20on%20those%20emails%20or%20help%2C%20or%20saying%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20let's%20talk%20about%20this%20and%20that%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20can%20help%20the%20team%20solve%20problems%20together%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20strange%20that%20I%20haven't%20heard%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarrios%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226b8e8b4d-0392-4e3b-9864-cf8367c59439%5C%22%3EA%20fix%20for%20bad%20one-on-ones%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBarrios%20might%20be%20onto%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-on-one-weekly-meeting-with-boss-mistakes-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMany%20one-on-one%20meetings%20are%20being%20done%20wrong%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20told%20Business%20Insider%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20often%2C%20one-on-one%20meetings%20become%20status%20updates%20dominated%20by%20the%20manager%2C%20missing%20the%20point%20entirely%2C%20said%20Steven%20G.%20Rogelberg%2C%20who's%20also%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Charlotte.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20the%20goal%20of%20these%20things.%20Because%20that%20serves%20the%20manager's%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERogelberg%20said%20one-on-one%20meetings%20were%20designed%20to%20meet%20workers'%20tactical%20and%20personal%20needs.%20Digging%20into%20personal%20needs%20means%20saying%20things%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BTell%20me%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20a%20boss%20could%20understand%20what%20a%20worker%20might%20need%20help%20with%20beyond%20a%20to-do%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20bosses%20were%20often%20skipping%20past%20the%20personal%20because%20that%20would%20take%20more%20work%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweekly-recap-email-ceo-tips-roblox-engineering-exec-sebastian-barrios-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749619717000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62b7219b9f5e550019aaa4f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweekly-recap-email-ceo-tips-roblox-engineering-exec-sebastian-barrios-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sebastian%20Barrios%20sends%20Roblox's%20CEO%20a%20weekly%20email%20outlining%20his%20accomplishments%2C%20what's%20next%20on%20his%20plate%2C%20and%20where%20he%20needs%20help.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmlee%40insider.com%20(Lee%20Chong%20Ming)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A74%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessins