t%20being%20LGBTQ%2B%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20at%20home%20with%20family%2C%20at%20work%2C%20on%20social%20media%2C%20or%20in%20public%20spaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20being%20%E2%80%9Cout%E2%80%9D%20looks%20different%20for%20everyone.%20Some%20people%20might%20be%20out%20only%20to%20close%20friends%20or%20family%2C%20while%20others%20might%20speak%20openly%20in%20public%20or%20on%20platforms%20to%20inspire%20others%20or%20push%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Dutee%20Chand%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20sprinters%2C%20in%202019%2C%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20athlete%20to%20publicly%20come%20out%20as%20lesbian.%20She%20shared%20that%20she%20was%20in%20a%20same-sex%20relationship%2C%20despite%20knowing%20that%20it%20might%20bring%20criticism%20and%20pressure.%20However%2C%20by%20coming%20out%2C%20Dutee%20not%20only%20lived%20her%20truth%20but%20also%20gave%20courage%20to%20others%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESide%20note%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EComing%20out%20should%20not%20be%20confused%20with%20another%20term%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Eouting%2C%20which%20is%20the%20act%20of%20revealing%20another%20person%E2%80%99s%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity%20without%20their%20permission.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Sometimes%20it%20can%20be%20done%20based%20on%20rumours%20or%20assumptions.%20It%20is%20not%20considered%20appropriate%20even%20when%20the%20intentions%20are%20good%20because%20it%20simply%20takes%20away%20one%E2%80%99s%20choice%20and%20their%20control%20and%20can%20even%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20discrimination%2C%20rejection%20or%20worse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESay%20this%2C%20not%20that%3A%20terms%20you%20should%20avoid%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20thoughtful%2C%20inclusive%20language%20shows%20respect%20and%20helps%20create%20a%20world%20where%20everyone%20feels%20seen%20and%20valued%2C%20which%20we%20can%20all%20support.%20Here%20are%20some%20ways%20that%20we%20can%20keep%20in%20mind%20while%20writing%20about%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20and%20try%20our%20best%20to%20avoid%20ambiguous%20ideas%20and%20concepts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodite%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20say%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20hermaphrodite%20is%20outdated%20and%20considered%20offensive.%20It%20wrongly%20suggests%20that%20someone%20has%20fully%20formed%20male%20and%20female%20reproductive%20systems%2C%20which%20is%20medically%20inaccurate%20and%20stigmatising.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20use%20%E2%80%9Cintersex%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20the%20respectful%20and%20accurate%20term%20for%20people%20born%20with%20physical%20sex%20traits%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20fit%20typical%20male%20or%20female%20categories.%20Also%2C%20avoid%20calling%20Hijras%20%E2%80%9Chermaphrodites%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F390947%2Fnoori-mohammad-abuse-transwoman-hiv-positive-india-children-shelter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHijras%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20are%20a%20distinct%20cultural%20and%20gender%20identity%20in%20South%20Asia%20and%20should%20be%20recognised%20on%20their%20own%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%9Chomosexual%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Chomo%2C%E2%80%9D%20simply%20ask%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHomosexual%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20clinical%20term%20that%20feels%20cold%20and%20impersonal%20to%20many%20in%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community.%20The%20shortened%20version%20%E2%80%9Chomo%E2%80%9D%20is%20often%20used%20as%20a%20slur%20and%20is%20offensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20ask%20how%20people%20would%20like%20to%20be%20addressed.%20These%20terms%20are%20affirming%20and%20widely%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon%E2%80%99t%20